# Contributing Guidelines

Thank you for your interest in contributing to this project!

## Pull Requests

- Fork the repository and create your branch from `main`.
- Make your changes with clear, descriptive commit messages.
- Before submitting a pull request (PR), ensure your code passes all tests and lint checks.
- Open a PR with a clear description of your changes and reference any related issues.

## Changelog

- **Update the `CHANGELOG.md` file** with a summary of your changes in the "Unreleased" section.
- Follow the existing changelog format for consistency.

## Review Process

- Your PR will be reviewed by maintainers.
- Please respond to feedback and make any requested changes.
- Once approved, your PR will be merged.

Thank you for helping improve this project!

## Issues

If you find a bug or have a feature request, please open an issue in the repository. Provide as much detail as possible, including:

- Steps to reproduce the issue
- Expected behavior
- Actual behavior
- Any relevant logs or error messages
- Environment details (e.g., OS, version of the project)
